The first available outpatient time slot for all noninvasive vascular studies was within 24 hours. The mean PII for the sample of 1695 tests in a 2-month period in 2010 was 3.23 hours (range < 1 minute to 70.80 hours; standard deviation [SD]±7.40). There was a significant difference in PII between WD (mean 2.30 hours SD ±4.62) and WE (16.59 hours SD ±18.64; P < .0001, Mann-Whitney test; Figure 1
). Ninety-nine percent of tests were read within 24 hours on WD compared to 76.5% on WE (P < .0001, 2-sided Fischer exact test; Figure 2
).
